"script": "Across your lifetime, you'll breathe in around 200 million liters of air. That's enough to fill more than 60 hot air balloons, each one big enough to lift a grown person off the ground. You see, you take about 20,000 breaths a day, pulling in roughly 11,000 liters without ever thinking about it. And every breath you take holds atoms once breathed by dinosaurs, kings, and total strangers thousands of years ago. So the air filling your lungs right now has been recycled through countless creatures before you, and one day, someone else will breathe the very atoms you just exhaled.",
